Rand, S. Africa Bonds Maintain Gain After September Inflation

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-10-19T08:12:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/rand-s-africa-bonds-maintain-gain-after-september-inflation.html
The rand maintained its advance
against the dollar and bonds remained stronger after South
African inflation for September was close to analysts’
estimates.  The currency of  Africa ’s biggest economy traded 0.2 percent
stronger at 7.9829 by 10:06 a.m. Johannesburg time, compared
with 7.9822 before the data were released. The 13.5 percent
government bonds due September 2015 maintained increases, with
the yield dropping four basis points, or 0.04 percentage point,
to 6.764 percent.  Consumer inflation accelerated an annual 5.7 percent in
September from 5.3 percent in August, Pretoria-based Statistics
 South Africa  said on its website today. The median estimate of
19 economists was for inflation to quicken to 5.6 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  